The paper deals with unsupervised feature learning algorithms based on convolutional formulations of independent components analysis (ICA) and their application to action recognition benchmarks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and sound (cs.SD).
